==Reception==
[[Steve Jackson (American game designer)|Steve Jackson]] reviewed ''Mission Escape!'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 44.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal| last= Jackson |first= Steve |author-link=Steve Jackson (American game designer)|date=October 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=44|pages=35}}</ref> Jackson commented that "on the whole, it's a great way to kill an evening.  Recommended for Apple owners who like reflex-testing games."<ref name="SG"/>

Graham Masters Jr. reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Mission Escape'' is one of a handful of games to combine arcade features with what is in reality a strategy game."<ref name="CGW1">{{cite magazine |last=Masters Jr. |first=Graham |title=Micro - Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=November–December 1981 |volume=1 |issue=1 |pages=30–31}}</ref>

